# What Happens When Fetch Fails?

Suppose:

```tsx
const response =
    await fetch(
        "https://wrong-api.com"
    );
```

You'll get an error.

Example:

```tsx
export default async function Page() {

    try {

        const response =
            await fetch(url);

        const data =
            await response.json();

        return (
            <div>
                {data.name}
            </div>
        );

    } catch {

        return (
            <p>
                Failed to load
            </p>
        );
    }
}
```

---

# Checking HTTP Status

A fetch can succeed but still fail.

Example:

```text
404
500
403
```

Always check:

```tsx
const response =
    await fetch(url);

if (!response.ok) {
    throw new Error(
        "Failed"
    );
}

return response.json();
```

